msgstr "sudo mysqladmin -u root password nuovapasswordrootsql"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2702(command) ../generic/server/C/databases.xml:95(command) ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:95(command)
msgid "sudo mysqladmin -p -u root -h localhost password newrootsqlpassword"
msgstr "sudo mysqladmin -p -u root -h localhost password newrootsqlpassword"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2706(para) ../generic/server/C/databases.xml:99(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:99(para)
msgid ""
"You can edit the <filename>/etc/mysql/my.cnf</filename> file to configure "
"the basic settings -- log file, port number, etc. Refer to "
"<filename>/etc/mysql/my.cnf</filename> file for more details."
msgstr ""
"È possibile modificare il file <filename>/etc/mysql/my.cnf</filename> per "
"configurare le impostazioni di base come file di log, numeri di porta, ecc. "
"Per maggiori informazioni, fare riferimento al file "
"<filename>/etc/mysql/my.cnf</filename>."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2715(para) ../generic/server/C/databases.xml:108(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:108(para)
msgid ""
"PostgreSQL is an object-relational database system that has the features of "
"traditional commercial database systems with enhancements to be found in "
"next-generation DBMS systems."
msgstr ""
"PostgreSQL è un database relazionale orientato agli oggetti che presenta le "
"caratteristiche di un database commerciale tradizionale e anche "
"miglioramenti dei sistemi DBMS di prossima generazione."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2722(para) ../generic/server/C/databases.xml:115(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:115(para)
msgid ""
"To install PostgreSQL, run the following command in the command prompt:"
msgstr ""
"Per installare PostgreSQL, eseguire il seguente comando dal terminale:"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2729(command) ../generic/server/C/databases.xml:122(command) ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:122(command)
msgid "sudo apt-get install postgresql"
msgstr "sudo apt-get install postgresql"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2733(para) ../generic/server/C/databases.xml:126(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:126(para)
msgid ""
"Once the installation is complete, you should configure the PostgreSQL "
"server based on your needs, although the default configuration is viable."
msgstr ""
"Una volta che l'installazione è completata, è possibile configurare il "
"server PostgreSQL a seconda delle proprie esigenze, sebbene la "
"configurazione predefinita sia abbastanza buona."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2741(para) ../generic/server/C/databases.xml:134(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:134(para)
msgid ""
"By default, connection via TCP/IP is disabled. PostgreSQL supports multiple "
"client authentication methods. By default, IDENT authentication method is "
"used. Please refer <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.postgresql.org/docs/8.1/static/admin.html\"> the PostgreSQL "
"Administrator's Guide</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"In modo predefinito, la connessione attraverso il protocollo TCP/IP è "
"disabilitata. PostrgreSQL supporta diversi metodi di autenticazione. Quello "
"predefinito è il metodo IDENT. Consultare <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.postgresql.org/docs/8.1/static/admin.html\">la guida "
"dell'amministratore PostgreSQL</ulink>."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2748(para) ../generic/server/C/databases.xml:141(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:141(para)
msgid ""
"The following discussion assumes that you wish to enable TCP/IP connections "
"and use the MD5 method for client authentication. PostgreSQL configuration "
"files are stored in the "
"<filename>/etc/postgresql/&lt;version&gt;/main</filename> directory. For "
"example, if you install PostgreSQL 7.4, the configuration files are stored "
"in the <filename>/etc/postgresql/7.4/main</filename> directory."
msgstr ""
"I passi seguenti assumono che si voglia abilitare la connessione TCP/IP e "
"che si desideri utilizzare il metodo di autenticazione MD%. I file di "
"configurazione di PostgreSQL sono nella directory "
"<filename>/etc/postgresql/&lt;version&gt;/main</filename>. Per esempio, se "
"si installa PostgreSQL 7.4, i file di configurazione sono nella directory "
"<filename>/etc/postgresql/7.4/main</filename>."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2758(para) ../generic/server/C/databases.xml:151(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:151(para)
msgid ""
"To configure <application>ident</application> authentication, add entries to "
"the <filename>/etc/postgresql/7.4/main/pg_ident.conf</filename> file."
msgstr ""
"Per configurare l'autenticazione <application>ident</application>, "
"aggiungere delle voci nel file "
"<filename>/etc/postgresql/7.4/main/pg_ident.conf</filename>."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2765(para) ../generic/server/C/databases.xml:158(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:158(para)
msgid ""
"To enable TCP/IP connections, edit the file "
"<filename>/etc/postgresql/7.4/main/postgresql.conf</filename>"
msgstr ""
"Per abilitare le connessioni TCP/IP, modificare il file "
"<filename>/etc/postgresql/7.4/main/postgresql.conf</filename>"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2767(para) ../generic/server/C/databases.xml:160(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:160(para)
msgid ""
"Locate the line <emphasis>#tcpip_socket = false</emphasis> and change it to "
"<emphasis>tcpip_socket = true</emphasis>. You may also edit all other "
"parameters, if you know what you are doing! For details, refer to the "
"configuration file or to the PostgreSQL documentation."
msgstr ""
"Localizzare la riga <emphasis>#tcpip_socket = false</emphasis> e modificarla "
"in <emphasis>tcpip_socket = true</emphasis>. Tutti gli altri parametri "
"possono essere modificati, ma bisogna sapere cosa si sta facendo. Per "
"maggiori informazioni, consultare la documentazione di PostgresSQL o fare "
"riferimento ai file di configurazione."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2775(para) ../generic/server/C/databases.xml:168(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:168(para)
msgid ""
"By default, the user credentials are not set for <emphasis>MD5</emphasis> "
"client authentication. So, first it is necessary to configure the PostgreSQL "
"server to use <emphasis>trust</emphasis> client authentication, connect to "
"the database, configure the password, and revert the configuration back to "
"use <emphasis>MD5</emphasis> client authentication. To enable "
"<emphasis>trust</emphasis> client authentication, edit the file "
"<filename>/etc/postgresql/7.4/main/pg_hba.conf</filename>"
